benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Retrieve bundle tags

covered: Valid requests / happy path: successful 200 responses and JSON array of Tag objects (default behavior excludes deleted tags).
Query parameters: includedDeleted=true/false, audit=FULL/MINIMAL, combination of includedDeleted + audit, extra/unexpected params handled, and invalid audit enum handled.
Empty response handling: existing bundle with no tags returns empty JSON array.
Path parameter validation & errors: invalid UUID -> 400, non-existent bundle -> 404.
Authentication failures: missing and invalid tokens return 401.
Security/input validation: injection/malicious payloads tested (400/422 expectations).
Regression/backwards-compatibility: deleted-tags regression and absence of audit parameter covered.
Non-functional/resilience: large-result performance, concurrency, resource-utilization and slow dependency/timeouts covered.
API availability: accessibility/unavailable endpoint behavior (503/504) tested.
gaps: Pagination: no tests covering pagination (page/size/offset) or documented behavior for paged results.
Rate limiting / throttling: no tests for burst requests / 429 responses or Retry-After behavior.
Caching / conditional GET: no tests for ETag, Cache-Control, If-None-Match / 304 Not Modified behavior.
Authorization (403) / permissions: no tests for authenticated-but-unauthorized users returning 403 or role-based access control.
Tag object schema validation: tests do not assert Tag JSON schema (required fields, types, nested audit structure) or validate audit payload contents precisely for FULL/MINIMAL.
Audit=NONE explicit behavior: absence of audit information is not asserted (absence vs minimal structure not verified).
Invalid includedDeleted values: non-boolean or malformed includedDeleted parameter cases are not tested.
Error response schema & headers: error payload shape, Content-Type, consistent error codes/messages and headers are not validated across error scenarios.
Server-side 5xx handling: explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenarios and recovery/retry behavior are not covered.
Concurrent modification consistency: race conditions where tags are added/removed during retrieval (consistency/atomicity) are not tested.
Content negotiation / Accept header: behavior for unsupported Accept values (e.g., 406) is not tested.
recommendations: Add pagination tests if supported (page/limit/offset boundaries, empty page, total counts); if pagination is not supported, add an explicit test asserting documented non-paginated behavior for large result sets.
Add rate-limiting tests that send bursts of requests to validate 429 responses, Retry-After header, and graceful degradation policies.
Add caching tests: assert presence/semantics of ETag and Cache-Control headers; test conditional GET with If-None-Match to get 304 Not Modified.
Add authorization/permission tests for authenticated-but-unauthorized users (expect 403) and ensure role-scoped access is enforced.
Validate Tag JSON schema with automated schema checks (id, tagDefinitionId, objectType, createdBy/updatedBy/timestamps) and assert audit structures for FULL vs MINIMAL and absence for NONE.
Add an explicit audit=NONE test (or assert on absence of audit information when audit param is omitted) to verify default behavior.
Test invalid includedDeleted values (e.g., includedDeleted=foo, includedDeleted=123) to ensure proper 4xx validation responses.
Standardize and validate error response bodies and headers across 4xx/5xx cases (Content-Type application/json, error code, error message fields, correlation id).
Introduce 5xx/server-failure simulations to verify monitoring/logging and client retry/backoff behavior.
Add tests for concurrent modifications (create/delete tags while retrieving) to validate consistency or document eventual consistency guarantees.
Add Accept header/content-negotiation tests (unsupported media types -> 406) and ensure Content-Type is consistently returned for success and error responses.
